1. after you remove the resource from Terraform state file, the order command you run that, it is been on tracked. So when you do the Terraform plan next time, if you see that the new resources, we are not trying to create it. When you run the Terraform plan, the resource will be created one. So how do you fix this drift?

terraform state rm 
does — removes from state only, not from AWS or main.tf!

main.tf    → has resource ✅
state file → removed ❌
AWS        → running ✅

refresh-only → updates EXISTING state entries
               with current AWS values

import       → ADDS missing resource
               back into state file

Your scenario → needs import first
                then refresh-only works

